- 2 garlic cloves crushed
- tsp ground cumin
- tsp ground coriander
- 1 tsp chilli flakes
- 1 tsp sweet paprika
- 2 tbsp finely chopped preserved lemon skin
- 140ml olive oil plus extra to finish
- 2 medium aubergines
- 150g fine bulgar
- 50g sultanas
- 10g fresh coriander chopped, plus extra to finish
- 50g pitted green olives, halved
- flaked almonds, toasted
- 3 spring onions
- 1 1/2 tbsp lemon juice
- 120g greek yoghurt
- salt


Prehear the oven to 200c/180c or gas mark 6

To make the chermoula, mix together in a small bowl the garlic, cumin, coriander, chili, paprika, presevred lemon 
and two thirds of the olive oil and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. 

Cut the aubergines in hald lengthways. Score the flesh of each hald with deep, diagonal criss-cross scores, making sure not to pierce the skin. 
Spoon the chermoula over each half, spreading it evenly, and place on a baking sheet cut side up. Put in the oven and roast for 40mins 
or untill the aubergines are completely soft. 
Meanwhile. place the bulgar in a large bowl and cover with 140m; boiling water. 

Soak the sultanas and add them to the bulgar, along with the ramaining oil. Add the herbs, olives, almonds, spring onion, 
lemon juice and a pinch of salt and stir to combine. 
Taste and add more salt if neccassary. 

Serve the aubergines warm or at room temperature. Place one half per prtion on a serving plate. Spoon bulgar on top, allowing some to fall from both sides. 
Spoon over some yoghurt, sprinkle with chopped cpriander and finish with a drizzle of oil. 
